Nexus	            8081	        changed from 8080
SonarQube	        9000	        fine



use an API Gateway (recommended later)

When you have several microservices, you can eventually add a gateway (like Spring Cloud Gateway or NGINX) to forward everything through a single port:

Frontend → Gateway (port 8080)
         ├── /users → user-service:7070
         ├── /timesheets → timesheet-service:7071
         ├── /leave → leave-service:7072
         └── /sickness → sickness-service:7073


That way your frontend only talks to one port.